Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgyJF1w65Fyqx1EG_ct4AaABAg,,@DavidStebbins,"The play that Casablanca was based upon, Everyone Comes to Rick's, was written before America joined WWII. Thus the line about everyone in America being asleep. Except for Humphrey Bogart (Rick), Dooley Wilson (Sam), and I think one other whom I can't remember, every actor credited in the movie was a European emigrant, even the ones who played Nazis. My favorite piece of trivia about the movie is that Ingrid Bergman was actually a couple inches taller than Humphrey Bogart so they took great pains in every scene to make him look taller. Sometimes he stood on a box, when seated they removed the couch cushions under her and asked her to slouch. It makes it fun for me on every rewatch to figure out what they did in every scene. There are so many great lines from this movie that have been quoted for decades.",2026-05-18T04:40:33Z,2026-05-18T04:40:33Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277786
