Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgzJI8bjKOH3rCjrzS14AaABAg,,@odysseusrex5908,"This is the greatest movie ever made. It is infinitely quotable and infinitely quoted.
The reason Rick was refusing to give them the letters was not that he wanted to keep Ilsa close to him but that he wanted to punish her for seemingly betraying him.
I think you missed what Louis was doing. He was using his position of power to force young women to sleep with him in return for exit visas. That is what he was doing with the young Bulgarian girl. What she wanted to know from Rick was whether Louis would actually give her and her husband their visas if she gave him what he wanted. Rick tells her he always has, but then goes and makes sure they get the money they need so their can be no doubt.
When Louis tells his men to round up the usual suspects, of course he knows who just shot Major Strasser tight in front of his eyes. He wants to cover up that fact and protect his friend. Also, he has just, finally, picked a side. You saw him open and then throw away a bottle of Vichy water. Vichy is a resort town in France known for its mineral springs. It was also the de facto capital of France after the government fled Paris. Throwing away the bottle represented his break with the Vichy government and decision to join the continuing fight against the Nazis.",2026-05-04T16:42:43Z,2026-05-04T16:42:43Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277960
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugys4qZ93P-0EF1L0sp4AaABAg,,@chipurBillWhite,"You’re just perfect for the reactor role for this film — and your accent is the cherry on the top. My favorite line/scene: “Of all the gin joints, in all the towns, in all the world, she walks into mine” The emotion behind it is intense.",2026-05-04T16:31:07Z,2026-05-04T16:31:07Z,0,False,1.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277963
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,UgwE0u-j5bWuDJLWR5F4AaABAg,,@quirtevans1977,"Ilsa was never in love with Laslo. When he professed his love for her she said ""Your secret is safe with me."" She never responded, ""I love you too."" She was in love with what he represented, not the man. She dropped Laslo as soon as she had the chance to go with the ""bad boy"" Rick. Fortunately for everyone, Rick took control of her.
Without direction and guidance from a man, women self-destruct. Wouldn't you agree?",2026-05-04T14:04:15Z,2026-05-04T14:04:36Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277966
