Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugyt4qFUfrs1Gz4eG2p4AaABAg,,@Jer-7007,"Well, I'm glad to see that you liked it.  But I doubt if anyone from your generation will understand the political context of the story (which would have been well understood by audiences of the time).  At this time, Casablanca (which is in Morocco) was a French colony.  But Germany had conquered France in WWII.  This meant that France, itself, was under German rule.  But French colonies (like Morocco) were kind of on their own.  That's why the French colonial police chief in this movie (Renault) , wants to enforce French law, but must kind of defer to his German masters - which he opposes sentimentally.  This is a delicate political situation,  well known to people of the time but that most people of this time wouldn't understand.",2026-05-04T09:47:30Z,2026-05-04T09:47:30Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277977
Casablanca,t2jBSAWCg5s,Ugx01kwBB0KmTJEGEFx4AaABAg,,@jollyrodgers7272,"Looks like she's never seen a globe before - LOL! (flat-earther?). Definitely one of the very best movies ever made. So much of the cast and the extras were actual refugees and expatriates from war-torn Europe. Remember, in 1942 the outcome of this war was far from determined. Yeah, this is almost non-stop dialogue - gotta pay attention. Claude Rains (Capt. Renault) is at his best. She's catching on nicely.👍😎👍",2026-05-04T09:05:13Z,2026-05-04T09:05:13Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:01:09.277979
