Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg.ABKSonVD4xDABLapaHulVy,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg,@TranLe-vy5nz,@ Thank you so much for your tips . I love all your videos❤️❤️❤️,2024-11-27T13:27:04Z,2024-11-27T13:27:04Z,0,True,,2026-05-19T02:01:37.375044
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg.ABKSonVD4xDABLbJdAbzw5,Ugx_uGmjXey5dDUuYeN4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,@TranLe-vy5nz Thank you! We are grateful to hear this. We appreciate your support more than you know! -Judy,2024-11-27T13:31:18Z,2024-11-27T13:31:18Z,1,True,,2026-05-19T02:01:37.375047
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgzFAbiub7FFe3dHkgt4AaABAg.AB84wkcaoojAB8uKKwqR10,UgzFAbiub7FFe3dHkgt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi @mannya4120, Thanks so much for watching. We visit the Sahara Desert for three days and spend 18 days in Fes. A link to the episodes from our 41-day trip is linked below. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2024-11-22T15:07:18Z,2024-11-22T15:07:18Z,0,True,,2026-05-19T02:01:37.455897
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,UgxvdwoxxlzzZwG8Qst4AaABAg.AB4SRAh4m1cAB4U4bnK0Dr,UgxvdwoxxlzzZwG8Qst4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"@priyankakamble12 Late February is considered shoulder season, which typically means that the prices are a bit lower than peak season. Marrakech and the Sahara Desert will have dry and sunny weather, although evenings and mornings will be cooler (lower 42°F (6°C)). Some places like Oukaimeden will potentially have snow, but the temperatures in Marrakech and Fes will be mild with daytime highs ranging from 63°F to 68°F (17°C to 20°C). Thanks for watching. Here is a link to our full series from our 41 days in Morocco. —Judy
🎥 Morocco Travel Series: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLNT98lWfwdF0_pL4S2LnqlBz2KBX9XMCc",2024-11-20T21:52:15Z,2024-11-20T21:52:15Z,0,True,,2026-05-19T02:01:37.657437
Marrakech,05QDGvi0_sM,Ugytz8bxr4jROsQzPLt4AaABAg.AB1p2a-8g5RAB1qrXPeTrA,Ugytz8bxr4jROsQzPLt4AaABAg,@FindingGinaMarie,"Hi @Judith-t8f, It is so much easier when you literally have no room. If you saw our episode in Marrakech when we first arrived, we made an effort to get rid of 12 pounds apiece of things in our suitcases. We have no room for extra stuff—and what we got rid of wasn't trinkets!—which does make it A LOT easier to say no. We also don't have a home base to decorate, so while it would be somewhat cool to collect things from all our travels, there's a freedom in spending our money on experiences versus stuff. Thanks so much for watching! —Judy
