Instagram,ZVEfS6yAIcc,Ugw4dLhipIIKIOhnrc14AaABAg,,@boyantrifonov,"12:30  Pat,I checked the accounts Brock Johnson mentioned. 

With the Wants and Needs (they literally have the word ""brand"" in their handle) but every reel starts differently and if you like their style you don't care that they promote their pant in the end. And you get the ""what are they going to do now?"" question in your head when you see a reel of theirs.

With Citizen the Artist you get a super cinematic short story that looks like a movie. The production quality is insanely high and yet things happen even in the short duration of the reel. This level of production is too much for a regular creator but they can still learn from the way the story is presented.

