Tourisme,tcGjKt8XRTI,Ugx-tPR-gm_sP0nNyZx4AaABAg,,@garyi.1360,"You guys are painting the tourist themselves as the problem.  It's not the tourist but the incorrect travel/planning concept that tourists mistaken follow.  And they do that because when reaching out for assistance what they get are these ridiculous 'package' plans that removes any education in a place from being necessary as it is when you make your own plans.  Tourists should not travel in these groups of strangers. What should be taxed and regulated are large brand hotels and tour agencies.  When individuals and small groups travel with their own planning and arrangements it's a much better experience.  As well is more adapted to how a local lives and behaves.  It's the tourism cattle culture that creates the masses coming all at once, bringing with them the oversized ships and coaches and people who don't have to lift their own bags and so size is not a factor. They simply become bulls in a China shop overwhelming each place they go.",2026-05-08T13:41:36Z,2026-05-08T13:47:47Z,0,False,0.0,2026-05-19T02:03:12.443196
